From 7532eeb40048757d26ec652c2700e696cbb3f9e4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Paramoshka <parfenov_ivan_42a@mail.ru>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 18:21:59 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] mark-based outbound interception for same-uid app/sidecar

Add mark-based interception mode as an opt-in alternative to the
owner-match (--uid-owner) approach, for environments where the sidecar
must run with the same UID/GID as the application container (e.g.
ingress-nginx under deckhouse, both UID 64535).

When traffic.sidecar.istio.io/outboundSocketMark is set, Envoy tags
its outbound sockets with SO_MARK (via cluster socket_options from
istiod) and iptables excludes marked packets via
'-m mark --mark <mark> -j RETURN' instead of '--uid-owner'. This
distinguishes Envoy from the app by socket mark rather than UID,
breaking the infinite outbound redirection loop.

UID transition to 64535 is intentionally NOT handled here; it belongs
to the deckhouse 003-change-to-deckhouse-user patch. This patch only
adds the mark plumbing and composes cleanly on top of 003.

Signed-off-by: Paramoshka <parfenov_ivan_42a@mail.ru>
